        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 2:45PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
south of Excelsior, moving northeast at 70 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Jethro...                         Charleston...
Arkola...                         Huntington...
Crossroads...                     Central City...
Witcherville...                   Dayton...
Milltown...                       Branch...
Excelsior...                      Vesta...
Cecil...                          Lonelm...
Ursula...                         Lavaca...
Altus...                          Mulberry...
Denning...                        Etna...

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 19 and
42.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
